article.headline: Louisiana-Lafayette 68, Lamar 65
article.story: LAFAYETTE, La. -- Josh Brown came off the bench to score 20 points and help Louisiana-Lafayette defeat Lamar 68-65 on Sunday, snapping a seven-game losing streak. The Ragin' Cajuns (2-8) led 55-43 after two free throws from David Perez with 10:02 left in the game, but a 3 from Lamar guard Kendrick Harris capped an 18-8 run and pulled the Cardinals to within two, 63-61, with 3:41 to go. A layup from Coy Custer cut Lamar's deficit to 66-65 with 20 seconds left to play, but the Cardinals were unable to score again. Charlie Harper scored 15 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead Lamar. The Cardinals (5-5) came into the game averaging 91.9 points per game -- the second-highest average in the country behind the Virginia Military Institute at 95.5 points per contest. The win for Louisiana-Lafayette is its first since a 91-66 victory over Division III Louisiana College on Nov.15.
